<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="section-SAC">
    <title>Stretches and Compressions</title>

    <p>
        For quadratic functions, vertical stretch is equivalant to a particular horizontal stretch. Then, we simply consider only the vertical stretch, of the form <m>f(x) = a(x - h)^2 + k</m>.
    </p>
</section>
